According to the media reports, a blast hit the capital of Afghanistan, leaving several dead and injured. Eyewitnesses reported an explosion in Kabul that killed two children and injured many others, RIA Novosti reported. According to the eyewitnesses, the incident was caused by a roadside bomb that targeted a Taliban vehicle in the Bagrami District. Police Issue Fine Over Banner On Financial Woes In Central… Prince Harry In Legal Fight To Pay For U.K. Police Protection Taliban officials have not yet commented on the incident, and no individual or group has claimed responsibility for the blast. Recently, Afghan media reported an explosion in the fourth security district of Kabul, the capital of the country. A car belonging to the Afghan police was also targeted in the center of Kabul last week.